<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <%- include('partials/head', { metaDescription: 'Privacy Policy for PictoCard - no account
    required, no persistent data storage, minimal data collection.', ogTitle: 'PictoCard - Privacy
    Policy', ogDescription: 'Privacy Policy for PictoCard.', ogUrl: domain + '/privacy',
    canonicalUrl: domain + '/privacy' }) %>
  </head>
  <body>
    <%- include('partials/header') %>

    <main class="container container-narrow prose">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="updated">Last updated: <%= lastUpdated %></p>

      <h2>1. Data We Collect</h2>
      <p>
        PictoCard is designed to minimize data collection. We do
        <strong>not</strong> store any emails, uploaded images, or personal information on our
        servers after your session ends.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Session Data</h2>
      <p>
        During the card-creation flow we temporarily hold the following in your browser session
        (server-side, in memory only):
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Your name and email address (for verification)</li>
        <li>The recipient's email or Discord username</li>
        <li>The uploaded image and card text</li>
        <li>The generated card image</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        This data is automatically discarded once the card is sent or the server restarts. It is
        never written to disk or a database.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Email Delivery</h2>
      <p>
        Emails are sent via
        <a href="https://resend.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Resend</a>, a transactional
        email service. When you send a card or request a verification code, your email address (and
        the recipient's email address where applicable) is transmitted to Resend for delivery.
        Resend may retain delivery logs in accordance with their own privacy policy, which can be
        found at
        <a href="https://resend.com/legal/privacy-policy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
          >https://resend.com/legal/privacy-policy/</a
        >. We send a verification code to the sender and the finished card to the recipient - no
        further email marketing is conducted.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Opt-out List</h2>
      <p>
        If you opt out via the <a href="/optout">opt-out page</a> your email address is added to an
        in-memory list that prevents cards from being sent to you. This list is also cleared on
        server restart and is never persisted.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Discord</h2>
      <p>
        If you connect your Discord account, we receive your Discord username and ID temporarily for
        the purpose of sending a card. No Discord data is stored beyond the current session.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Cookies</h2>
      <p>
        We use a single session cookie to track the card-creation flow. No advertising or tracking
        cookies are used.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        For privacy-related inquiries please open an issue on our
        <a href="https://github.com/larsenv/pictocard" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
          >GitHub repository</a
        >.
      </p>
    </main>

    <%- include('partials/footer') %>
  </body>
</html>
ml>
